<subSubSection id="1A22068AB797C8E2BC58EDE5BEAE0521" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AE11740522BB92C87D705E90FD8F65AF" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB6D69DD67F053372440B5B3FD563441" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">It is distributed in the laterite hills of Northern Kerala in Peninsular India.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4533E08D708208D1AFB280B2077EC230" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="D5932741FAD9EF1FACAC2DFF29085D1A" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC45844829A0932B3DECFD57875DE3BA" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
The specimens were collected from the Madayipara, a lateritic hillock in Kannur District of Kerala, at latitude 12°2'N and longitude 75°16'E (
<geoCoordinate id="BC430779EE516C3B3DC3550D56AD7393" degrees="12" direction="north" minutes="2" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="12.033334">12°2'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="060BDF38D49CEE3ACDEB647F515A2918" degrees="75" direction="east" minutes="16" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="75.26667">75°16'E</geoCoordinate>
), and with an altitude of 40-47 msl. It is a notable area being the type locality of some narrow endemics such as 
<taxonomicName id="7F9391A2BFE220F04107CFA6E2D038DF" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Menyanthaceae" genus="Nymphoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="krishnakesara">
<emphasis id="FFDE1FF871E1A683699585CEFB62B2B4" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Nymphoides krishnakesara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="21A6764247C2F45D7F70A9FC98D09325" author="Joseph, KT" journalOrPublisher="Botany" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" pagination="281 - 284" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1756-1051.1990.tb01773.x" refId="B3" refString="Joseph, KT, Sivarajan, VV, 1990. A new species of Nymphoides from India. Nordic J. Botany 10: 281 - 284, 10.1111/j.1756-1051.1990.tb01773.x" title="A new species of Nymphoides from India. Nordic J." url="10.1111/j.1756-1051.1990.tb01773.x" volume="10" year="1990">Joseph and Sivarajan 1990</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="0C9D2CA88C9CA285C09DE8F57493F243" authorityName="A. K. Pradeep, K. T. Joseph &amp; V. V. Sivarajan" authorityYear="1990" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lythraceae" genus="Rotala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="malabarica">
<emphasis id="B02A2351A6C4F0CB82DDCADF3B12E50B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Rotala malabarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FDE367B2CE49643941619CBB4E23FBC4" author="Pradeep, AK" journalOrPublisher="Sinica" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" pagination="51 - 61" refId="B9" refString="Pradeep, AK, Joseph, KT, Sivarajan, VV, 1990. Rotala malabarica a new species of Lythraceae from India. Bot. Bull. Acad. Sinica 31: 51 - 61" title="Rotala malabarica a new species of Lythraceae from India. Bot. Bull. Acad." volume="31" year="1990">Pradeep et al. 1990</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="D3973160D1F5793773B8C44C7FAF92DE" authorityName="A. K. Pradeep &amp; V. V. Sivarajan" authorityYear="1991" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ekakusuma">
<emphasis id="25E128BAA6F07BD2EC664D0044408E91" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Justicia ekakusuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5301DE838FD7173923DE5810986F4795" author="Pradeep, AK" journalOrPublisher="Rheedea" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" pagination="40 - 43" refId="B8" refString="Pradeep, AK, Joseph, KT, Sivarajan, VV, 1991. Justicia ekakusuma a new species of Acanthaceae from Peninsular India. Rheedea 1: 40 - 43" title="Justicia ekakusuma a new species of Acanthaceae from Peninsular India." volume="1" year="1991">Pradeep et al. 1991</bibRefCitation>
)and 
<taxonomicName id="5ECA451C5C93323D203245B9B188821D" authorityName="P. V. Madhusoodanan &amp; N. P. Singh" authorityYear="1992" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Lepidagathis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="keralensis">
<emphasis id="9019E3259595D05C1190FDD1DCEC9B6F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Lepidagathis keralensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7DA45F8C474BBBCF243CF5363EF5793F" author="Madhusoodanan, PV" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" pagination="19 - 22" refId="B4" refString="Madhusoodanan, PV, Singh, NP, 1992. A new species of Lepidagathis (Acanthaceae) from south India. Kew Bulletin 1: 19 - 22" title="A new species of Lepidagathis (Acanthaceae) from south India." volume="1" year="1992">Madhusoodanan and Singh 1992</bibRefCitation>
). The lateritic outcrops of this area support a grassland-scrub system, unique in its ecology, being active along with the monsoon rains, supporting rich assemblages of many aquatic and semi-aquatic plants and animals, and remaining as barren land as the rain recedes (
<bibRefCitation id="75A06680954BBBA9F4D0E78F4FE46E1B" author="Palot, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Cobra" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" pagination="3 - 6" refId="B6" refString="Palot, MJ, Radhakrishnan, C, 2002. Herpetofauna of Madayipara hill, Kannur district, Kerala. Cobra 48: 3 - 6" title="Herpetofauna of Madayipara hill, Kannur district, Kerala." volume="48" year="2002">Palot and Radhakrishnan 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CD54462A2F3735149817ED98F1049A53" author="Palot, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Cobra" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" refId="B7" refString="Palot, MJ, Radhakrishnan, C, 2005. Faunal diversity of a laterite hill system at Madayipara, Kannur district, Kerala State, India. Rec. Zool. Surv. India Occ. Paper No. 242. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, 1-98." title="Faunal diversity of a laterite hill system at Madayipara, Kannur district, Kerala State, India. Rec. Zool. Surv. India Occ. Paper No. 242. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, 1 - 98." year="2005">2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A253BF8BE9E64BA8D642A0FD2062BB17" author="Balakrishnan, VC" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" refId="B2" refString="Balakrishnan, VC, Palot, MJ, Rajesh, KP, 2010. Observations on the flora of Madayipara a midland laterite hill in Kannur district, Kerala. Malabar Trogon 8 (2&amp;3): 14-29." title="Observations on the flora of Madayipara a midland laterite hill in Kannur district, Kerala. Malabar Trogon 8 (2 &amp; 3): 14 - 29." year="2010">Balakrishnan et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). More than 500 species of plants were recorded from the area, which includes 59 Peninsular Indian endemics, of which 14 are narrow endemics of Kerala state, confined to the laterite hillocks (
<bibRefCitation id="9FA3539BFDC3169F672582B49B933B85" author="Balakrishnan, VC" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" refId="B2" refString="Balakrishnan, VC, Palot, MJ, Rajesh, KP, 2010. Observations on the flora of Madayipara a midland laterite hill in Kannur district, Kerala. Malabar Trogon 8 (2&amp;3): 14-29." title="Observations on the flora of Madayipara a midland laterite hill in Kannur district, Kerala. Malabar Trogon 8 (2 &amp; 3): 14 - 29." year="2010">Balakrishnan et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="62E8F9328995364FF5FDE948755CC72E" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7482E530160A06259EDD4796A6528834" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Eriocaulon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also well represented in Madayipara with five species, 
<emphasis id="397923E60541248C0A23ECCCC3CC9CC1" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">viz</emphasis>
., 
<taxonomicName id="70970E458840A3D7DFF8D62A416C366D" authorityName="Dalzell" authorityYear="1851" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis id="10D9815C2E293DADBBF75376FB3F7AEE" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Eriocaulon cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="64392FD62C54D3F0889028F8F669FA01" authorityName="Steud" authorityYear="1855" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="heterolepis">
<emphasis id="141655BC3C055D078F995E08B014417D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Eriocaulon heterolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1027591D05F4C567C22A0E56721DD3B7" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="lanceolatum">
<emphasis id="DEB03BF12B9D365D3052ABB6A551ED97" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Eriocaulon lanceolatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BE8339D37F6FD27E718754CF47E4D421" authorityName="R. Ansari &amp; N. P. Balakr" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Fyson" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="parviflorum">
<emphasis id="7ABC9E1E83D19D1EE669135ACDA642FA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Eriocaulon parviflorum</emphasis>
