and 
<taxonomicName id="04423E517CCBC089C629D4595E6856A3" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Eriocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="xeranthemum">
<emphasis id="9DE63417A51507C45244061A5A6B7A76" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Eriocaulon xeranthemum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The present species is growing in wet areas of Madayipara, along with species such as 
<taxonomicName id="0626E53465BD36A02B5819CAE34EFE87" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lentibulariaceae" genus="Utricularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="reticulata">
